history.content: The schedule for Spring comes out around October so you'll have to wait it out and see. I don't think much can be said about future class offerings right now.

Neel - I normally teach it in Fall, but I have so many sabbatical credits accrued that the university

will start taking them away from me if I don't use them, so I'm taking a sabbatical for Fall semester.

It is unlikely that I'll be teaching it in spring, but there's still some possibility of that.

Normally you could take ME 119 in Fall and get a pretty similar course, but it turns out that Prof. Lin

is teaching ME 102B instead. :(

So the last option is to take EE247B in Spring with Prof. Nguyen. I think that he regularly accepts

undergraduates in that class.  I'm sorry that things worked out this way.

From what I've seen, EE147 is usually offered in the fall, but it doesn't look like it is being offered next semester based on the EE Fall 2018 Class Schedule. I was hoping to take this class before I graduate so does anyone know if there are plans to offer this class in spring of 2019?
history.subject: EE147 Offering
